summary: This is a U.S. Department of Justice foreign travel questionnaire for an Assistant U.S. Attorney (AUSA) from the Southern District of New York (SDNY) traveling from New York to an unspecified foreign location from February 3-6, 2020. The purpose is to interview and debrief a witness in the ongoing, sensitive investigation into Jeffrey Epstein, with Ghislaine Maxwell identified as a subject.

keyFacts: The document is a foreign travel authorization form for an SDNY AUSA traveling from February 3-6, 2020, for the Jeffrey Epstein investigation.
The stated purpose of the travel is 'interviewing and debriefing a witness' in the ongoing and 'very sensitive' investigation.
Ghislaine Maxwell is explicitly named as a subject of the investigation, with her multiple citizenships (U.S., U.K., France) noted.
The travel party includes the AUSA, two other AUSAs, an FBI Special Agent, and an NYPD Detective, indicating a multi-agency effort.
The case is referenced with the USAO number 2018R01618, confirming active DOJ work on the Epstein case in early 2020.
